CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 14, 1959, pg. A3, reads: First-Prize Winners - Happy about receiving first prize of a $75 Savings Bone, the Moore brothers (Alfred, Samuel and Calvin), a very cool and down trio, show their pleasure, following the judges announcement, last Friday night, at the NAACP Youth Council talent show, held at Westinghouse High School. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Brothers Alfred Moore, Samuel Moore, and Calvin Moore holding savings bond, at Westinghouse High School for NAACP Youth Council talent show
